00:03:30.700 --> 00:03:34.780
In film noir, you know you're going to get heavy shadows and a dark, mysterious story

00:03:35.020 --> 00:03:40.140
In romances, you know you're always gonna get two people who share their emotions and their feelings to grow closer

00:03:40.380 --> 00:03:43.880
So, why can't these limitations work for the genre of found footage?

00:03:43.880 --> 00:03:46.640
Now true, this has been used in comedies and dramas

00:03:46.640 --> 00:03:49.260
so it's probably more appropriate to call it a sub-genre

00:03:49.260 --> 00:03:54.680
but it's still a distinct style with a distinct look that many film makers have added their own touch to

00:03:55.300 --> 00:04:00.220
